The paper proposes a method to improve the generative adversarial network (GAN) by introducing the concept of normalized diversity, which aims to unfold the manifold of unknown topology and non-uniform distribution. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and graphics (cs.GR).
